        "URL": "data:text/html;charset=utf-8,%3C!doctype%20html%3E%0A%3Chtml%20lang%3D%22%22%3E%0A%3Chead%3E%0A%20%20%3Cmeta%20charset%3D%22utf-8%22%3E%0A%20%20%3Ctitle%3EThe%20Soviet%20Union%20and%20the%20United%20States%3C%2Ftitle%3E%0A%3C%2Fhead%3E%0A%3Cbody%3E%0A%3Cbody%3E%3Ch1%3EThe%20Soviet%20Union%20and%20the%20United%20States%3C%2Fh1%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3E%0ARelations%20between%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20and%20the%20United%20States%20were%20driven%20by%0Aa%20complex%20interplay%20of%20ideological%2C%20political%2C%20and%20economic%20factors%2C%0Awhich%20led%20to%20shifts%20between%20cautious%20cooperation%20and%20often%20bitter%0Asuperpower%20rivalry%20over%20the%20years.%20%20The%20distinct%20differences%20in%20the%0Apolitical%20systems%20of%20the%20two%20countries%20often%20prevented%20them%20from%0Areaching%20a%20mutual%20understanding%20on%20key%20policy%20issues%20and%20even%2C%20as%20in%0Athe%20case%20of%20the%20Cuban%20missile%20crisis%2C%20brought%20them%20to%20the%20brink%20of%0Awar.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0AThe%20United%20States%20government%20was%20initially%20hostile%20to%20the%20Soviet%0Aleaders%20for%20taking%20Russia%20out%20of%20World%20War%20I%20and%20was%20opposed%20to%20a%20state%0Aideologically%20based%20on%20communism.%20%20Although%20the%20United%20States%20embarked%0Aon%20a%20famine%20relief%20program%20in%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20in%20the%20early%201920s%20and%0AAmerican%20businessmen%20established%20commercial%20ties%20there%20during%20the%0Aperiod%20of%20the%20New%20Economic%20Policy%20(1921-29)%2C%20the%20two%20countries%20did%20not%0Aestablish%20diplomatic%20relations%20until%201933.%20%20By%20that%20time%2C%20the%0Atotalitarian%20nature%20of%20Joseph%20Stalin's%20regime%20presented%20an%0Ainsurmountable%20obstacle%20to%20friendly%20relations%20with%20the%20West.%20%20Although%0AWorld%20War%20II%20brought%20the%20two%20countries%20into%20alliance%2C%20based%20on%20the%0Acommon%20aim%20of%20defeating%20Nazi%20Germany%2C%20the%20Soviet%20Union's%20aggressive%2C%0Aantidemocratic%20policy%20toward%20Eastern%20Europe%20had%20created%20tensions%20even%0Abefore%20the%20war%20ended.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0AThe%20Soviet%20Union%20and%20the%20United%20States%20stayed%20far%20apart%20during%20the%20next%0Athree%20decades%20of%20superpower%20conflict%20and%20the%20nuclear%20and%20missile%20arms%0Arace.%20%20Beginning%20in%20the%20early%201970s%2C%20the%20Soviet%20regime%20proclaimed%20a%0Apolicy%20of%20dtente%20and%20sought%20increased%20economic%20cooperation%20and%0Adisarmament%20negotiations%20with%20the%20West.%20%20However%2C%20the%20Soviet%20stance%20on%0Ahuman%20rights%20and%20its%20invasion%20of%20Afghanistan%20in%201979%20created%20new%0Atensions%20between%20the%20two%20countries.%20%20These%20tensions%20continued%20to%20exist%0Auntil%20the%20dramatic%20democratic%20changes%20of%201989-91%20led%20to%20the%20collapse%0Aduring%20this%20past%20year%20of%20the%20Communist%20system%20and%20opened%20the%20way%20for%20an%0Aunprecedented%20new%20friendship%20between%20the%20United%20States%20and%20Russia%2C%20as%0Awell%20as%20the%20other%20new%20nations%20of%20the%20former%20Soviet%20Union.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cimg%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22coop.html%22%3E%3Cimg%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlease%20follow%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22coop.html%22%3Eguided%20tour%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20have%20a%20look%20at%20one%20of%0Athese%20showcases%3A%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%0A%3Ca%20href%3D%22coop.html%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22coop.html%22%3EEarly%20Cooperation%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22party.html%22%3ESoviet%20and%20American%20Communist%20Parties%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22wartime.html%22%3EWorld%20War%20II%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22coldwar.html%22%3ECold%20War%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%0AWhen%20you%20have%20seen%20them%20all%2C%20walk%20down%20the%20stairs%2C%0Aback%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22entran